<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>You may be out of luck.........</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Chris">Chris</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:26 p.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> You may be out of luck.........<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1503" TARGET=_self>Do factions actually work like they should?</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Problems due to racial faction can be changed easily, but rogues and necroes simply have places they will never be able to purchase. Basically if they say "damn necroes\rogues I'll dont deal with your kind", then you are likely screwed. No matter how many kobolds you kill or quests you do, you will still be the class that is hated. Not positive on this, but thats the way its been for pariah classes and Verants comments in beta suggest it's meant to be. Social negatives are a large part of why certain classes are rated as high difficulty.

<P>Anyway you are rping an insane homicidal necromancer, merchant should be a little wary of dealing with you:)
<P>&gt; A Necromancer is hated by all and can't even purchase from his
<BR>&gt; own merchants, yet as I read on about faction standings, it is
<BR>&gt; possible to change this. In Ak'anon, merchants won't sell to you
<BR>&gt; (that is if you pick gnome like I did). So if I kill obsolete
<BR>&gt; models in basements and kobolds outside, this should increase my
<BR>&gt; faction standing and in end actually let me shop?
<P>&gt; I tried this and didn't work at all, was this function disabled
<BR>&gt; in beta phase 4?
<P>&gt; Or am I doing something bad?
<P>&gt; Because way it is now people who start as gnome necromancers
<BR>&gt; can't even purchase cloth armor.. I mean not the whole sets and
<BR>&gt; its very hard to even buy a staff or other neat things.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
